1.4 Creating Df

isro_budget <- data.frame(Year = 1999:2020,
                           Initial_Budget = c(1766,2019,2030,2263,2368,2731,3148,3610,3859,4074,4959,
                                              5778,6626,6715,6792,7238,7388,7509,9094,10783,12473,13479),
                           
                          Revised_Budget = c(1726,1909,1909,2164,2274,2540,2675,2997,3290,3499,4167,
                                              4880,4432,4880,5172,5826,6959,8045,9155,11200,12473,13479),
                          
                          GDP_growth = c(8.85, 3.84, 4.82, 3.80, 7.86, 7.92, 7.92, 8.06, 7.66, 3.09, 7.86, 8.50, 5.24, 5.46, 6.39, 7.41, 8.00, 8.26, 7.04, 6.12, 5.02, 5.02),
                           
                          Party = c("BJP","BJP","BJP","BJP","BJP","Congress","Congress","Congress",
                                     "Congress","Congress","Congress","Congress","Congress","Congress",
                                     "Congress","BJP","BJP","BJP","BJP","BJP","BJP","BJP")
           ) %>% 
  
                          mutate(lag_values = lag(Initial_Budget, default = 0),
                                 budget_growth_rate = round((Initial_Budget - lag_values) / Initial_Budget * 100, 2))
                        

                          isro_budget$budget_growth_rate[1] <- 0

1.5.1 congress

change_in_congress <- isro_budget %>% 
  filter(Party == "Congress") %>% 
  summarise(max(Initial_Budget) - min(Initial_Budget)) %>% pull()

change_in_congress

change_in_congress_perc <- change_in_congress / pull(isro_budget %>% 
                                                    filter(Year == 2004) %>% 
                                                    select(Initial_Budget)) * 100

2.1 Type 1

2.1.1 static graph

party_budget_race <- isro_budget %>% 
    ggplot(aes(x=Year, y=Initial_Budget, col = Party) ) +
    geom_path(aes(group = 1), arrow = arrow(type = "closed")) + 
    # geom_vline(xintercept = c(2004,2014), col = c("red")) +
  
    theme_classic() +
    labs(title = "ISRO Budget allocation wrt Political Party in Power",
         subtitle = "created by ViSa") +
    theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5, face="bold"),
          plot.subtitle = element_text(hjust = 0.5, face="italic", color="maroon"),
          legend.position = "bottom") +
    ggeasy::easy_plot_title_size(size = 16) +
  
    scale_x_continuous(breaks = breaks_width(2),
                       expand = c(0.15, 0)) +
    scale_y_continuous(breaks = breaks_width(2000), 
                       labels =label_dollar(prefix = "\u20b9", suffix = " Cr") ) +

    directlabels::geom_dl(aes(label = Party), method = list("last.points"))
